description: Modifies the specified managed prefix list. Adding or removing entries in a prefix list creates a new version of the prefix list. Changing the name of the prefix list does not affect the version. If you specify a current version number that does not match the true current version number, the request fails.

parameters.name: PrefixListId
parameters.description: The ID of the prefix list.

parameters.name: AddEntries
parameters.description: One or more entries to add to the prefix list. (dict) --- An entry for a prefix list. The CIDR block. Description (string) --- A description for the entry. Constraints: Up to 255 characters in length.

nested_params.name: Description
nested_params.description: A description for the entry. Constraints: Up to 255 characters in length.

parameters.name: RemoveEntries
parameters.description: One or more entries to remove from the prefix list. (dict) --- An entry for a prefix list. The CIDR block.

parameters.name: MaxEntries
parameters.description: The maximum number of entries for the prefix list. You cannot modify the entries of a prefix list and modify the size of a prefix list at the same time. If any of the resources that reference the prefix list cannot support the new maximum size, the modify operation fails. Check the state message for the IDs of the first ten resources that do not support the new maximum size.

nested_items.name: PrefixListId
nested_items.description: The ID of the prefix list.

nested_items.name: State
nested_items.description: The current state of the prefix list.

nested_items.name: PrefixListArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) for the prefix list.

nested_items.name: PrefixListName
nested_items.description: The name of the prefix list.

nested_items.name: MaxEntries
nested_items.description: The maximum number of entries for the prefix list.

nested_items.name: Version
nested_items.description: The version of the prefix list.

nested_items.name: Tags
nested_items.description: The tags for the prefix list.

nested_items.name: OwnerId
nested_items.description: The ID of the owner of the prefix list.
